pageContext.claim: “But we're setting records in so many ways including record unemployment meaning in a positive way.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump never achieved record unemployment and by the time of this interview he no longer had bragging rights to a nearly 50-year low. The Bureau of Labor Statistics reported on Feb. 1 that the unemployment rate increased to 4 percent in January. The unemployment rate in December was no longer at a 49-year low, but an 18-year low. Now the rate is merely the best since the beginning of 2018.
